name: partitionMap
signature: { <A, B, C>(f: (a: A) => Either<C, B>): (self: List<A>) => [left: List<B>, right: List<C>]; <A, B, C>(self: List<A>, f: (a: A) => Either<C, B>): [left: List<B>, right: List<C>]; }
description:
Partition a list into two lists, where the first list contains all elements
for which the specified function returned a `Left`, and the second list
contains all elements for which the specified function returned a `Right`.
